U016Q117G67.message:
Gm Community!
@Salim Virani ’s mention came as a such peaceful and reinforcing msg to just keep the energy up. As a health practitioner I was laughed at when pointed the importance of nature for health. Left that position. As a gardner I was laughed at when pointed the importance of managed forests for a community raised for generations among pastures and cattle, without vacations or retirement plan. In web2 communities of "environmentalists" being discredited when calling the importance of web3 and crypto models. I was kinda frustrated. Have been thinking that the problem was my poor abilities to communicate my ideas.
Then I arrived here, and there’s so much resonance. I don't even have to debate. People already know, and those with a little less field experience are open minded enough to understand the potential of web3 for inter generational achievements. I just resonate with the words and dreams of people like @Christina Trout Christina, @Tagan Horton, @Djimo Serodio, @Salim Virani , @LCC , @Yamine , @Sistla V Abhishek, @李枝蔚Zhiwei, @cryptowanderer and many others, I get really hopefull for the future of my kids while reading all those intros. Maybe the the bounds of our souls can become our Global Community and the soulbound nfts can be our passport. Don’t know, just thinking out loud. Thank you so much Kernel team for putting it all together and for all the participants for dedicating some of your time for new emerging possibilities.

