U01JJFB16RG.message:
Ok, phew :sweat_smile:

@Harold Davis I have colonised your notes :wink: <https://kernel.community/conversation/>

Please forgive me? If you can, please also consider adding to, editing and in any way you please extending this beginning? I would be happy to collaborate on this new section of the Kernel site...

@Sparrow Read if you feel inspired, perhaps the artists' interpretation of this, and the fact of creativity in the face of alienation and the other aspects of that quote which stood out for you could be compiled into another page in this section?

The site is in an open GH repo: <http://github.com/andytudhope/kernel|github.com/andytudhope/kernel> though I will, of course, be happy to convert any document you send me into the appropriate form if you don't feel comfortable running it locally :pray: Once we have discussed this a bit, edited it and made the correct and appropriate changes to all my appropriation, we can post it in the general channel and invite further collaboration...

@Sparrow Read thank you so much. I agree and appreciate what you have added. Would you like me to put this into a piece, or are you happy to keep honing it until you feel it's right and are ready to submit a PR/doc for me? My one thought is about the danger of exclusive focus. That is, while I agree that the ground itself is always experiential, I do think that it must be balanced by some kind of rigor. How to come to this without falling into the trap of a will to power or attempt to control/make legible is my question. If we say it's _only_ about experience, then there are no reasonable grounds on which to engage meaningfully and we end up in the so-called New Age.

@Sebnem wonderful to have you back :pray: thank you for this insightful pattern re-cognition: it is deeply helpful for me.

&gt; I'm still unable to formulate what this is about, what is it that "practically" we're talking about.
Your scare quotes indicate the understanding that what we're talking about is not practical in the general meaning of that word (for this reason, by the rule of complementary opposites, it is the only truly practical knowledge we can cultivate). What we're talking about is, in a profound way, far less important than the fact we are talking. That's meta Level 1. First, we develop awareness of awareness. Then, we recognise that the fact we're talking is most critical, but what we are saying is also genuinely important - not in terms of our own opinion, but in terms of seeing ourselves more clearly (i.e. my realisation about synthesis and power was a major moment for me - meta Level 2). Awareness of awareness of awareness. It is this doubly-aware mind which sees that the drive to connect with the other is a part of seeing our own self more clearly: for the more intimate and immediate the connection, the clearer the mirror.

Self-recursively honing awareness through dialogue, through lived contemplation in honest reflection with others, is a large part of how I experience interactions like this. Awareness bent back on itself with skill eventually "disappears". There is the open field beyond right or wrong. There is 'satori': a sudden and ecstatic insight into the ground of your own being. There is the silence which comes home to stay in a heart that has been emptied of all its images, leaving only the unconditional love which is its nature; its origin and destiny. There there are no more formulas, no more words...

@Sparrow Read Yes @Holly Grimm is in the email thread, along with Magenta! Just double checked with Magenta that we get the invite to her. :purple_heart: Ty kindly for this, guess an overlooked benefit of consensus is self organizing coordination :pray::skin-tone-5: (this was several hrs in too!) Would you like to join us as well btw?
Yes, Susan's story is very powerful &amp; indicative of experiences usually gone unheard, her first time sharing was last Reconstitution, and was just as riveting every second. Again, ty kindly for your appreciation of the range of voices &amp; the space for them.
We've learned a lot from the Longhouse's commitment to the process. Yesterday was great example, Everyone was likely on few hrs of sleep from previous night's Black wampum ceremony, class &amp; celebrating Angele's bday :joy:

